<http://example.org/tennis/player/Carlos_Alcaraz> <http://example.org/tennis/provenance/evidenceText> "Alcaraz easily qualified for the French Open and reached the third round, where he was defeated by Jan-Lennard Struff." .
<http://example.org/tennis/tournament/French_Open> <http://example.org/tennis/provenance/evidenceText> "He became the first man to win majors on clay, grass, and hard courts in the same year, and the first to win the French Open, Wimbledon, and the US Open in the same year since Rod Laver in 1969.[178]" .
<http://example.org/tennis/player/Kwon_Soon_woo> <http://example.org/tennis/provenance/evidenceText> "At Wimbledon, he earned his 80th win at each major with a first-round victory over Kwon Soon-woo, becoming the first player to do so.[274]" .
