<http://example.org/tennis/tournament/French_Open> <http://example.org/tennis/provenance/evidenceText> "These tournaments are held clay and grass courts, respectively, surfaces very different from each other,[71] usually being held a few weeks from each other,[185] meaning that players who have deep runs in the French Open have little time to adapt to the different surface conditions found at Wimbledon.[186][187]" .
